body:
@aljoscha Ah right, for the new timestamps we will definitely need a 0.10-specific consumer if we want to use them. I think it makes sense to include a new module then.

This current PR does not respect the new 0.10 timestamps ( @radekg please correct me if I'm wrong here ), but I think we can add this as a separate follow up JIRA / PR afterwards, because it'll probably require changing some code in the `flink-connector-kafka-base` and the user-facing deserialization schemas, which will need more discussion.

I'll find time this week to give this PR a test.
